@startuml "BusinessUseCases"
' Business Use Case model (UML business modeling / RUP notation)
' Business actors and business use cases use the <<business>> stereotype.
' In hand-drawn UML these carry a diagonal slash; here we mark them with <<business>>.

left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam actorStyle awesome

title SourceFlow.AI Business - Business Use Case Model (v2: notación corregida)

actor "Dueño de PyME" as owner <<business actor>>
actor "Cliente Final" as customer <<business actor>>
actor "Mistral AI" as mistral <<support / system actor>>

rectangle "SourceFlow.AI  (Business)" {
  usecase "UCB-01\nConvertir documentación\nen respuestas dinámicas" as UCB1 <<business use case>>
  usecase "UCB-02\nGestionar precisión\nde respuestas (RAG)" as UCB2 <<business use case>>
  usecase "UCB-03\nAutomatizar\natención al cliente" as UCB3 <<business use case>>
  usecase "UCB-04\nEscalar ventas\n(respuestas inmediatas)" as UCB4 <<business use case>>
}

owner --> UCB1
owner --> UCB3
customer --> UCB3
customer --> UCB4
owner ..> UCB4 : <<benefit>>

UCB1 ..> mistral : <<support>>
UCB2 ..> mistral : <<support>>
UCB1 ..> UCB2 : <<include>>\n(RAG anti-alucinaciones)

note bottom
  RB-RAG-01 (Evitar alucinaciones): UCB-01 debe usar
  obligatoriamente arquitectura RAG; cada respuesta queda
  anclada a la documentación base.
  Notación: actores y casos de uso de negocio llevan el
  estereotipo <<business>> (slash diagonal en UML dibujado a mano).
end note
@enduml
